That log is from a modded install and there are a few things obviously wrong:

You have two copies of the Firespitter plugin: one in GameData, and one in GameData\Firespitter\Plugins. It should only be in it's own folder.

There's a copy of one of the Infernal Robotics plugins in GameData. It looks like you don't have the rest of it installed at all, so just delete it.

Something is going seriously wrong with RasterPropMonitor. It's producing more than 60,000 NullReferenceExceptions, but they may be a result of the incorrectly installed plugins.

Did you upload that log before installing and launching the game with those mods?

Try this:

  1. Delete your output log.
  2. Delete everything from GameData except the NASAmission and Squad folders. At a minimum, Kerbal Alarm Clock, Vanguard Technologies EVA Parachutes, and one other mod (can't tell which, but I suspect FAR or B9) are installed incorrectly.
  3. Reinstall the mods following the included instructions or the instructions in the How to Get Support sticky.
  4. Delete old versions of Module Manager.
  5. Launch the game, cause the problem, and quit.
  6. Upload the output log.
Also, it won't hurt to remove older versions of ModuleManager. I don't know when it was fixed, but previous 2.X.X versions didn't play nicely with each other.
